# Private app slug denylist — copy this file to `.private-slugs` and edit.
#
# `.private-slugs` is gitignored. The private-slug guard
# (scripts/check_private_slugs.py) reads it at runtime and blocks any
# commit — and fails CI — that stages one of these slugs in a tracked
# file. build-loop is open source; this keeps the maintainer's private
# project names out of every tracked file, including the guard itself.
#
# Format:
#   - one slug per line
#   - blank lines and `#` comments are ignored
#   - each line is a case-insensitive regex fragment, matched as a
#     word-ish token (so `example-app` will not match `examples`)
#   - escape regex metacharacters: write a literal dot as `\.`
#
# The guard FAILS CLOSED: if `.private-slugs` is missing or empty when
# run in CI / `--all` mode, it exits non-zero rather than passing.
#
# The entries below are placeholders — replace them with your real
# private slugs in your local `.private-slugs`.
example-app
example-ios-app
example-web-app
example\.com
